Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.31,0:00:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.41,0:00:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.68,0:00:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.82,0:00:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.90,0:00:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.91,0:00:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.56,0:00:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.70,0:00:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.89,0:01:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.95,0:01:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.73,0:01:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order to bring back Mokuba's memories, Kaiba used his Blue-Eyes in the final battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.57,0:01:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Noah took advantage of Kaiba's feelings and beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.62,0:01:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now he's turned the\N both of them into stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.05,0:01:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Noah, I won't let\N you get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.89,0:01:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll inherit both Kaiba's pride as a Duelist and Mokuba's sadness!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.28,0:01:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's battle, Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.36,0:01:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you want to call yourself the true winner, defeat {\b0}me{\b1} first!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.04,0:01:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Inherited Deck: Yugi VS Noah"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.55,0:02:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll be creating a new deck to match your deck type.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.90,0:02:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Yugi... You use a Strategical Deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And Seto used a Power Deck, designed to call forth powerful Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.09,0:02:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're mixing together two completely different deck types.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.56,0:02:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Trying to make a strategy with the both of your cards together will only serve to slow you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.79,0:02:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What was that light just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After Shinato appeared, the Ark of Miracles' Effect disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.26,0:02:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So all the cards used before have been returned to the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.35,0:02:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even with the ark's Effect gone, Yugi still has no Monsters on the field and no cards in his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.37,0:02:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Noah's Deck Master\N has 3300 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.38,0:02:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Yugi doesn't draw a Monster Card this turn, Yugi's gonna be wiped out! OOH-AH~!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.06,0:02:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.33,0:02:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.50,0:03:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.09,0:03:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you decided to back out last minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.64,0:03:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let you change\N your Deck Master if you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.86,0:03:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not necessary!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.66,0:03:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can feel it clearly... Kaiba and Mokuba's heart beat pulsing in this deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.75,0:03:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes, Kaiba! Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.22,0:03:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My friends, walk with me down this road!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.56,0:03:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.69,0:03:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Illusion Beast Gazelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.71,0:03:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! He got a Monster out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.72,0:03:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as expected, your luck is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.68,0:03:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you could call it "delaying the inevitable."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But regardless of whether you called a Monster out, if {\i1}I {\i0}get a Monster now, this Duel is done!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.46,0:03:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.26,0:03:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, too bad for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems you're going to have to wait a while before finishing me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.28,0:03:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My my absolute advantage\N hasn't changed a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.78,0:03:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Shinato, King of Heaven, will attack you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.06,0:04:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six Paths of Reincarnation!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be! My Monster should have been in Defense Position...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.65,0:04:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did my Life...?\N Was it...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct. Shinato's Special Ability just activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.92,0:04:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Shinato destroys one of the player's Defense Position Monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.80,0:04:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their Life Points halve as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.64,0:04:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And thanks to Shinato's Deck Master Ability, the damage the player received gets added to {\i1}my{\i0} Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Deck Master is totally unfair! OOH-AH-OOH!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.80,0:04:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all! This Duel was hopeless from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I can't comprehend your suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.73,0:04:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you take on such a reckless Duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.70,0:04:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you and Seto not enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.42,0:05:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. Me and Kaiba are rivals!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.80,0:05:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just may be enemies bound to fight by a fate driven for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.73,0:05:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't let that hurt what's even more important than that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm? And what would {\i1}that{\i0} be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.76,0:05:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the bonds between Duelists!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bonds"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.35,0:05:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.52,0:05:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a ridiculous answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You used Mokuba...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You chose to use cheap methods, while Kaiba chose to fight you fairly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.13,0:05:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All Duelists are bound by the same desire to protect their pride!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll take those bonds!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll beat you with them!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.99,0:05:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My... turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.09,0:05:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll place a Monster in face-down Defense Position! My turn is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.10,0:05:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You pulled another Monster Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.27,0:05:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder how long you can survive this Duel relying on luck alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.32,0:05:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pity you, Yugi.\N It looks like this turn will be your last.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's past time I show you what my deck is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the Spirit Monster Yata-Garasu on the field in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.55,0:06:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Spirit Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.10,0:06:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! I start things off by attacking with Shinato, King of Heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six Paths of Reincarnation!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! That elf...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.26,0:06:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrained Elf Swordsman can't be destroyed in battle by any Monster holding 1900 Attack Points or higher, Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.19,0:06:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His luck disgusts me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.33,0:06:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I activate the Magic Card Element Fountain from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Element Fountain increases my Life by 500 points every time a Monster returns from the field to a plater's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.94,0:06:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return, Yata-Garasu!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.50,0:07:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Element Fountain activates this very moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.01,0:07:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Life rises by 500 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the heck did he return a Monster to his hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. Yata-Garasu!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That card is part of the rumored Spirit Series I've been hearing about!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.55,0:07:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.76,0:07:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus of Industrial Illusions once traveled to the Orient of far Eastern lands, where he learned of ancient Japanese mythology.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.03,0:07:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a legendary series was inspired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the more distinguishing features of the Spirit Monsters is an Effect they all share.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.09,0:07:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirit Monsters are unable to be Special Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.73,0:07:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they are returned to your hand at the End Phase of the turn they are Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.53,0:07:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! Element Fountain was created as part of a combo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.16,0:07:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if his Life Restoration isn't in effect now that Ark of Miracles is gone, his Life Points still increase thanks to his Spirit Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.68,0:07:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with that, my turn comes to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.69,0:07:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is Kaiba's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's currently inside of his Deck Master, and on the field as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.60,0:08:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba, I may be able to beat him using your card.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.03,0:08:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place a Monster in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.29,0:08:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.93,0:08:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will Summon a Spirit Monster known as Asura on this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.66,0:08:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asura, attack Retrained Elf Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thousand Handed Knives of Hell!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.40,0:08:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrained Elf Swordsman's Special Ability only activates when up against Monsters who hold under 1900 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the Effect can't be activated against Asura, who holds only 1700 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.43,0:08:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now be gone!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I also activate Asura's Special Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.88,0:09:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monsters got more swords, like he's going to attack again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.30,0:09:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asura's Special Ability allows him to attack every single Monster on your side of the field every turn it attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.32,0:09:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with all your Wall Monsters gone, you'll be defenseless!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.75,0:09:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all I need in order to defeat you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.34,0:09:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you'll learn your place once you realize I've beaten you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Asura!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.06,0:09:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thousand Handed Knives of Hell!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.07,0:09:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.54,0:09:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it, Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.71,0:09:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The card you just attacked was a card Kaiba left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.14,0:09:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Cyber Pod!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.73,0:09:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cyber Pod is a card that destroys all Monsters on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.42,0:09:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All{\i0} Monsters on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.55,0:09:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Noah, that includes {\i1}you{\i0} as well, as you've merged with your Deck Master and you're now on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.96,0:10:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome, Yugi! You just pulled off a huge comeback!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.47,0:10:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Yugi wins!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.35,0:10:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booyah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate my Deck Master's Final Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.00,0:10:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reincarnation of Soul!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.57,0:10:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.70,0:10:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi-{\i1}san{\i0} won, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be! He's safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.65,0:10:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean that you were unaffected by Cyber Pod's Effect?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.33,0:10:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means I was {\i1}careless{\i0}, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.42,0:10:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I had to use my Deck Master's Final Ability against you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.72,0:11:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reincarnation of Soul is activated the moment the Deck Master is targeted for destruction on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.66,0:11:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an Ability that negates that Card Effect and returns the Deck Master to his original position on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.75,0:11:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the cost of me not being able to call Shinato to the field again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah, Cyber Pod's Effect isn't through yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.69,0:11:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both players draw five cards from their respective decks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.87,0:11:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You then Special Summon any low-level Monster Cards among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.35,0:11:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Special Summon Critter and Magnet Warrior Gamma in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.03,0:11:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now go on and Summon your Monster Cards already, Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, Yugi...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.04,0:11:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck's wrong with Noah now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.17,0:11:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}can't{\i0}, isn't that {\i1}right{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Part of the requirements for using a Spirit Monster is that it can't be Special Summoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.77,0:11:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.07,0:11:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Magnet Warrior Gamma and Critter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.59,0:11:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This automatically activates Critter's Special Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.60,0:12:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can add any Monster Card with 1500 Attack Points or less from my deck to my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I add Big Shield Gardna to my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Monster I Summon to the field is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.84,0:12:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.56,0:12:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Black Magician?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.86,0:12:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah, your field is empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.86,0:12:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, Black Magician!\N Direct Attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.68,0:12:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice move, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.40,0:12:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you figure out the drawbacks of Noah's Spirit Monsters, coming up with a strategy is easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.12,0:12:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job, Yugi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.83,0:12:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.63,0:12:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Noah?\N This match is just getting started!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.69,0:13:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, how {\i1}dare{\i0} you {\i1}humiliate{\i0} me like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.20,0:13:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humiliate"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.79,0:13:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all the humiliation you and Gozaburo put Kaiba and Mokuba through, you have no room for mouthing off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.27,0:13:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the world I created!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.69,0:13:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of what you {\i1}ants{\i0} think, it's completely unforgivable to harm {\i1}me{\i0}, the {\i1}creator{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.25,0:13:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of a creator that uses people as stepping stones!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.96,0:13:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah, everyone has a home for their soul to return!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.19,0:13:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A home for their soul to return...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.07,0:13:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that steel sun is {\i1}not{\i0} the home you're meant to return to!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah! I'm going to release your soul through this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence, Yugi!\N {\i1}I'm{\i0} the one who's going to eliminate {\i1}you{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.48,0:13:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.57,0:13:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.20,0:13:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Word!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.06,0:14:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.44,0:14:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Magic Card reflects the image of one chosen Monster on the field in the Rug of Hell
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.49,0:14:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and using that spiritual energy, I can Normal Summon a Spirit Monster with the same Level from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.97,0:14:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the card I choose to Summon is the Spirit Monster, Yamata Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.92,0:14:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.42,0:14:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is {\i1}that{\i0} thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's got 2600 Attack Points, OOH-AH! OOOH-AHHH!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat this! Scotching Flame Thrower!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.11,0:14:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my Deck master Ability activates.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.92,0:14:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return, Yamata Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because a Monster just returned to my hand, Element Fountain activates.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.40,0:15:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Life goes up by an additional 500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that Shinato is gone, that outrageous Effect that cuts your Life in half is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.35,0:15:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but all the damage I inflicted on him...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.82,0:15:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, you've got a mere 100 Life Points remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.49,0:15:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can you do with {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.79,0:15:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! Yugi, you just have to believe in yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.85,0:15:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, you're just getting warmed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I still have a small 1% chance of victory, I'll keep on believing in this deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.34,0:15:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.60,0:15:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card Sealing Swords of Light from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How fearsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.26,0:16:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Sweet move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now he's on even ground with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oooh-ah! OOH!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.82,0:16:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing great, Yugi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.49,0:16:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sealing Swords of Light stops him from attacking for three turns! 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let this chance slip by, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.30,0:16:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you telling me this group is responsible for raising his spirits?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll also Summon Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuriboh! Direct Attack Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.28,0:16:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something touch me just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.08,0:16:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an utterly pitiful attempt at an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.50,0:16:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Stand there, helplessly prodding your head for a way to attack me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I hereby make a prophecy sating:\N "The moment the Sealing Swords of Light ware off..."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.03,0:16:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...you will be killed in an instant!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.79,0:17:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There hasn't been a {\i1}single{\i0} prophecy I've stated that hasn't come true in this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.80,0:17:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place a Monster face-down in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.69,0:17:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then end my turn as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the first turn of Sealing Swords of Light is done and over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.67,0:17:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.18,0:17:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Black Magician Girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unfortunately, I can only activate my Deck Master, Kaiser Sea Horse's Special Ability for Light Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't use his Deck Master Ability to Summon the Magician Girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.63,0:17:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For now, I just need to focus on getting a Monster on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Shield Gardna in Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I pull Kuriboh into Defense Mode as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.74,0:17:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That puts an end to my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.70,0:17:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.34,0:17:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon a Monster face-down in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.56,0:17:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then set a card face-down, ending my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.03,0:17:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've now made it to the second turn of Sealing Swords of Light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.75,0:17:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:18:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}None of the cards in my hand can turn this around!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll set one card face-down and finish my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think you only got a couple of cards out, despite the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.62,0:18:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only have one more turn before my prediction becomes a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.96,0:18:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you mentally prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.67,0:18:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up, Yugi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.51,0:18:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi {\i1}will{\i0} win this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.56,0:18:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, dammit! OOH!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.81,0:18:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cuz we believe in him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.53,0:18:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh, such foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.78,0:18:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you believe in a victory with no supportive reasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need reasoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.09,0:18:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't expect a lonely bastard like you who's been alone your whole life to understand how we feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.35,0:18:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our willingness to believe in the bonds we share has turned the impossible into the possible time and time again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph. Just as Seto had Mokuba, Yugi has you guys by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.63,0:18:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't allow that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to test whether your "bonds" are truly what you say they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.75,0:18:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.47,0:19:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OTOGI!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.56,0:19:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a great look on his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.03,0:19:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when Yugi loses, you'll all have the same expressions!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.16,0:19:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could almost call him {\i1}lucky{\i0} to not have to feel the terror you guys will suffer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard! How could you go this far!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment Yugi's Life Points hit zero, 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.52,0:19:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you fools will rue the day you ever believed in such a pathetic Duelist 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.82,0:19:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the very bottom of your hearts!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.03,0:19:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the whole lot of you will remain permanently trapped in those wave of emotions, 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.17,0:19:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just as Seto and Mokuba stand before you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.97,0:19:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And while surrounded by your frozen bodies, a look of hatred planted on his face...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I wish you could stay like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.90,0:19:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see you trapped with that look on your face {\i1}forever{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.29,0:19:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what exactly is so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.59,0:19:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pitiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.93,0:19:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your spirit hasn't matured at {\i1}all{\i0} since the time of your accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still just as childish as ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.32,0:19:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at every one of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.54,0:20:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, we believe in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not scared of you, even with your cheap tricks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.69,0:20:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with... their eyes...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.61,0:20:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah, burn this image deep in your mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.12,0:20:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are eyes that believe in the bonds we hold dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to send you all to hell one by one!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.60,0:20:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.90,0:20:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.44,0:20:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pyro Clock of Destiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The Sealing Swords of Light...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.47,0:20:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pyro Clock of Destiny is a Trap Card that pushes the turn count of our Duel ahead by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've lost your barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.53,0:20:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place a Monster in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.04,0:20:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Otohime!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.88,0:20:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then activate Otohime's Special Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.05,0:20:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Otohime is Summoned, I can change the Battle Position of any Monster on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:20:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one to feel that effect...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.12,0:21:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...will be {\i1}you{\i0}, Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Kuriboh's been forced into Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.01,0:21:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then sacrifice Otohime and my face-down Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.45,0:21:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Yamata Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.18,0:21:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, our match has been decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.43,0:21:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack, Yamata Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.82,0:21:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now vanish from my sight, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.48,0:21:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi knocks Noah down with an incredible attack from his Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Noah just recovers his Life Points using his Deck Master Ability and his Life Recovery Combo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.97,0:21:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now his Life Value has reached 10,000!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.18,0:21:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Noah begins turning us to stone one by one at the end of his turns!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.15,0:21:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still have faith in him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.79,0:22:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Yugi's victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.34,0:22:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.05,0:22:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"1000 Life Points VS 100!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.68,0:22:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.17,0:22:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.08,0:22:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.35,0:22:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.03,0:22:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.42,0:22:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.98,0:22:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.57,0:22:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.34,0:23:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.49,0:23:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.30,0:23:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.06,0:23:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
